  (29, ' Siaran Pers - PT Link Net Tbk Dengan Merek First Media Terus Konsisten Menyediakan Layanan Yang Terbaik Kepada Pelanggan', NULL, ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/linknet-default-old.png', ' siaran-pers-pt-link-net-tbk-dengan-merek-first-media-terus-konsisten-menyediakan-layanan-yang-terbaik-kepada-pelanggan', ' Siaran Pers - Pt Link Net Tbk Dengan Merek First Media Terus Konsisten Menyediakan Layanan Yang Terbaik Kepada Pelanggan', NULL, ' Muhammad Daffa Prayodi', ' <h2 align="center">GUGATAN PT FIRST MEDIA TBK. (KBLV) TIDAK TERKAIT DENGAN LAYANAN FIRST MEDIA PENYEDIA LAYANAN TV KABEL DAN&nbsp;<em>HIGH SPEED BROADBAND CABLE INTERNET</em></h2>

<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Jakarta, 9 November 2018 &ndash;&nbsp;</strong>PT Link Net Tbk (LINK) dengan merek First Media, pemimpin di industri penyedia TV kabel dan&nbsp;<em>High Speed Broadband Cable Internet</em>&nbsp;terus konsisten menyediakan layanan berkualitas bagi pelanggan. Penetrasi TV berbayar serta akses ke&nbsp;<em>fixed broadband internet</em>&nbsp;yang masih rendah membuat industri ini memiliki potensi yang sangat baik. Karena itu, First Media terus berkomitmen untuk meningkatkan kualitas layanannya dan memperbanyak akses masyarakat ke jaringan First Media.</p>

<p>Menyangkut pemberitaan di media massa terkait gugatan PT First Media Tbk (KBLV) ke PTUN adalah mengenai lisensi layanan telekomunikasi nirkabel PT First Media Tbk (KBLV) dan tidak berhubungan dengan layanan dan lisensi First Media yang dioperasikan oleh PT Link Net Tbk (LINK).<br />
Layanan yang dioperasikan oleh PT First Media Tbk (KBLV) adalah layanan internet berbasis nirkabel dengan menggunakan teknologi&nbsp;<em>4G LTE</em>; sedangkan, layanan First Media yang dioperasikan oleh PT LinkNet Tbk (LINK) adalah layanan TV kabel &amp;&nbsp;<em>High Speed Broadband Internet</em>&nbsp;berbasis kabel menggunakan teknologi&nbsp;<em>Hybrid Fiber Coaxial (&ldquo;HFC&rdquo;)</em>&nbsp;yang adalah teknologi yang menggabungkan kabel koaksial dan kabel serat optik (<em>fiber</em>) sebagai medium penghantar, serta teknologi Fiber-To-The-Home (<em>&ldquo;FTTH&rdquo;)</em>, yang adalah teknologi dengan menggunakan&nbsp;<em>full&nbsp;</em>kabel serat optik (<em>fiber)&nbsp;</em>sebagai medium penghantar.<br />
Dengan demikian, pemberitaan di media massa tersebut tidak berdampak apapun terhadap layanan First Media yang dinikmati oleh pelanggan saat ini.</p>

<p>Strategi First Media untuk terus memberikan nilai lebih bagi pelanggan adalah dengan terus berinovasi baik dari sisi produk TV kabel dan<em>&nbsp;High Speed Broadband Cable Internet</em>, serta peningkatan kualitas layanan yang terus menerus. Selain itu, First Media juga akan terus memperluas jangkauan layanannya ke kota-kota lain di Indonesia, dimana saat ini layanan First Media telah dapat dinikmati di beberapa kota yaitu: Jabodetabek, Surabaya dan sekitarnya, Bandung dan sekitarnya, Malang, Bali, Medan, dan Batam.<br />
Hal ini sesuai dengan misi dari First Media yaitu meningkatkan kualitas hidup masyarakat Indonesia dengan menyediakan layanan dan solusi yang inovatif dan berkualitas untuk TV kabel dan&nbsp;<em>broadband cable internet</em>.</p>', NULL, TRUE, ' PT Link Net Tbk (LINK) dengan merek First Media, pemimpin di industri penyedia TV kabel dan High Speed Broadband Cable Internet terus konsisten menyediakan layanan berkualitas bagi pelanggan. Penetrasi TV berbayar serta akses ke fixed broadband internet yang masih rendah membuat industri ini memiliki potensi yang sangat baik. Karena itu, First Media terus berkomitmen untuk meningkatkan kualitas layanannya dan memperbanyak akses masyarakat ke jaringan First Media.', NULL, ' 2021-11-29 19:40:46', ' 2026-05-27 16:41:03', ' 2018-11-10', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (31, ' Link Net Achieves 2 Million Homes Passed And Shareholders Approve Share Buy Back', NULL, ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/Link-Net-Achieves-2-Million-Homes-Passed-And-Shareholders-Approve-Share-Buy-Back-_1_.webp', ' link-net-achieves-2-million-homes-passed-and-shareholders-approve-share-buy-back', ' Link Net Achieves 2 Million Homes Passed And Shareholders Approve Share Buy Back', NULL, ' Muhammad Daffa Prayodi', ' <p>Jakarta,</p>

<p>January 15, 2018</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>PT Link Net Tbk</strong>&nbsp;(&ldquo;<strong>Link Net</strong>&rdquo; or the &ldquo;<strong>Company</strong>&rdquo;; stock code: &ldquo;LINK&rdquo;) announced that it achieved 2 million total homes passed as at the end of 2017. Link Net&rsquo;s shareholders also approved a share buyback at its extraordinary general meeting (&quot;<strong>EGM</strong>&quot;) on Monday the 15<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;of January 2018.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>At their public expose after the EGM, Link Net reported a strong finish to 2017 to achieve a total network size of over 2 million homes passed. This is more than an additional 170,000 homes passed for the year and comfortably beat their guidance of 150,000 homes passed in 2017.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>At their EGM on Monday morning the 15<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;of January, the company&rsquo;s shareholders approved a share buyback scheme with a price up to Rp6,000 per share, maximum size up to 7.1% of paid-up capital, for a period of 18 months starting from the 15<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;of January 2018, in line with regulatory requirements.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>The Company also proposed and subsequently shareholders approved administrative changes to two of their articles of association in compliance with capital markets legislation.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Irwan Djaja, President Director and CEO, commented on the results, said:&nbsp;<em>&ldquo;Achieving 2 million homes passed is a significant milestone for Link Net. This is due to the continual hard work and diligence of our rollout, operational and technology divisions. The investment is made possible due to the consistent strong execution of our sales and marketing divisions. They ensure that network utilization remains high across our network thus providing a quick payback on our investment&quot;.</em></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Moreover, Irwan Djaja said<em>: &ldquo;The approval of the share buyback, up to Rp6,000 per share, reflects a strong vote of confidence for Link Net&rsquo;s prospects from shareholders.&rdquo;</em></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong><u>About PT Link Net Tbk</u></strong></p>

<p>PT Link Net Tbk (&quot;Link Net&quot;), established in 1996, is the largest provider of services via cable in Indonesia, providing subscription of high quality television services, high-speed next generation broadband internet, and data communications. Link Net operates in Greater Jakarta, Greater Surabaya (including Malang), Bandung, Bali, Medan and Batam.</p>

<p>Link Net owns and operates a network of Hybrid Fiber Coaxial cable (&quot;HFC&quot;) and Fiber-to-the Home (FTTH) that provide high-speed internet access services to retail and business customers. Link Net also operates a subscription television channel in collaboration with PT First Media Television (&ldquo;FMTV&rdquo;), its subsidiary.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Learn more at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ir.linknet.co.id/" target="_blank">www.ir.linknet.co.id</a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><em>For further information, please contact:</em></p>

<p><strong>Joel Ellis</strong></p>

<p><strong>Head of Investor Relations</strong></p>

<p><strong>PT Link Net Tbk</strong></p>

<p>Tel: +62 812 911 77785</p>

<p>Email:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:Joel.Ellis@linknet.co.id">Joel.Ellis@linknet.co.id</a></p>', NULL, TRUE, NULL, NULL, ' 2021-12-02 01:05:34', ' 2026-05-27 18:38:05', ' 2018-01-16', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (33, ' Link Net Shareholders Approve Appointment Of Directors, Approve Reduction In Issued And Paid Up Capital & Approve Increasing The Maximum Number Of Shares That Can Be Purcahsed Via The Company’s Share Buyback Plan', NULL, ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/LINK-NET-SHAREHOLDERS-APPROVE-APPOINTMENT-OF-DIRECTORS_-APPROVE-REDUCTION-IN-ISSUED-AND-PAID-UP-CAPI.webp', ' link-net-shareholders-approve-appointment-of-directors-approve-reduction-in-issued-and-paid-up-capital-approve-increasing-the-maximum-number-of-shares-that-can-be-purcahsed-via-the-company’s-share-buyback-plan', ' Link Net Shareholders Approve Appointment Of Directors, Approve Reduction In Issued And Paid Up Capital & Approve Increasing The Maximum Number Of Shares That Can Be Purcahsed Via The Company’s Share Buyback Plan', NULL, ' Muhammad Daffa Prayodi', ' <p>Jakarta</p>

<p>December 20, 2018</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>PT Link Net Tbk (&ldquo;<strong>Link Net</strong>&rdquo; or the &ldquo;<strong>Company</strong>&rdquo;; stock code: &ldquo;<strong>LINK</strong>&rdquo;)</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Link Net Shareholders have approved the appointment of Wonbae Lee as a director and Suvir Varma as an independent director. Wonbae Lee is currently a principal at CVC Capital Partners focusing on Asia Operations. In a career spanning 20 years, Wonbae has held senior executive roles across finance, consulting and healthcare. This includes his role as Head of Asia Life Science and Core Imaging at General Electric, and President of AstraZeneca in Indonesia. Wonbae has successfully led large teams of professionals and will be instrumental in driving further value creations for Link Net. Suvir Varma, is an ex Senior Partner of Bain &amp; Company, where he led the firm&rsquo;s business focused on Financial Investors across Asia Pacific. He has more than 20 years of experience across consulting and finance-related roles focusing on strategic developments and operational improvements. We warmly welcome both Wonbae and Suvir to our board of directors and look forward to utilizing their robust skills and expertise across our business.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Shareholders acknowledge the resignation of director Timotius Sulaiman effective as of June 2018 and approved the resignation of director Edward Sanusi along with the resignation of independent director Surya Tatang. Shareholders also approved the resignation of commissioner Lorne Somerville. We would like to thank Timotius Sulaiman, Edward Sanusi and Surya Tatang for their strong leadership on our board. We would also like to thank Link Net commissioner Lorne Somerville who has provided strong support and supervision in his role. Shareholders approved the resignation of Sigit Prasetya from his position as a director of Link Net and further approved Sigit Prasetya&rsquo;s new role as a commissioner of Link Net. We look forward to Sigit&rsquo;s continued guidance as a commissioner of the Company.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Until 30 November 2018, Link Net had 130,908,300 treasury shares. Link Net&rsquo;s shareholders approved the reduction of issued and paid up capital by 130,908,300 shares by share withdrawal derived from the shares bought back by the Company. Upon approval by the Ministry of Law and Human Rights, Link Net&rsquo;s issued and paid up capital will be reduced from 3,042,649,384 to 2,911,741,084 shares.<br />
Shareholders approved the additional number of shares that can be purchased via the Company&rsquo;s buyback by a further 75,146,002. The maximum number of shares that can be purchased are 291,174,108, at a maximum buyback price of Rp6,000 per share.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>The Company&rsquo;s President Director and Chief Executive Officer, Mr. Marlo Budiman, commented on the meeting: The approval of reducing the Company&rsquo;s issued and paid up capital and approving the additional buyback is expected to be value accretive for shareholders by incrementally increasing the shareholders percentage ownership of the Company and by increasing the Company&rsquo;s earnings per share. Appointing two new high caliber and internationally experienced directors highlights Link Net management&rsquo;s continual focus on driving shareholder returns through efficient capital management and recruiting high quality employees.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong><u>About PT Link Net Tbk</u></strong></p>

<p><br />
PT Link Net Tbk (&quot;<strong>Link Net</strong>&quot;), owns and operates a high-speed broadband network in Indonesia, offering high speed internet and cable tv to both residential and enterprise clients.</p>

<p><br />
Learn more at&nbsp;<a href="http://ir.linknet.co.id/">www.ir.linknet.co.id</a></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>For further information, please contact:</p>

<p><br />
Joel Ellis<br />
Head of Investor Relations<br />
PT Link Net Tbk<br />
Tel: +62 812 911 77785<br />
Email:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:joel.elis@linknet.co.id">Joel.Ellis@linknet.co.id</a></p>', NULL, TRUE, ' Link Net Shareholders have approved the appointment of Wonbae Lee as a director and Suvir Varma as an independent director. Wonbae Lee is currently a principal at CVC Capital Partners focusing on Asia Operations. In a career spanning 20 years, Wonbae has held senior executive roles across finance, consulting and healthcare. This includes his role as Head of Asia Life Science and Core Imaging at General Electric, and President of AstraZeneca in Indonesia.', NULL, ' 2021-12-02 01:29:13', ' 2026-05-27 14:31:37', ' 2018-12-21', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (34, ' Link Net Concludes Annual General Meeting Of Shareholders--shareholders Approve Record Dividend Payment Of Rp674 Billion, A 60% Dividend Payout Ratio Of Normalized Net Earnings--shareholders Approve Appointment Of New Director And New Commissioner', NULL, ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/Link%20Net%20Concludes%20Annual%20General%20Meeting%20Of%20Shareholders-2019.jpeg', ' link-net-concludes-annual-general-meeting-of-shareholders-shareholders-approve-record-dividend-payment-of-rp674-billion-a-60-dividend-payout-ratio-of-normalized-net-earnings-shareholders-approve-appointment-of-new-director-and-new-commissioner', ' Link Net Concludes Annual General Meeting Of Shareholders--shareholders Approve Record Dividend Payment Of Rp674 Billion, A 60% Dividend Payout Ratio Of Normalized Net Earnings--shareholders Approve Appointment Of New Director And New Commissioner', NULL, ' Muhammad Daffa Prayodi', ' <p>April 26, 2019</p>

<p>PT Link Net Tbk (&ldquo;Link Net&rdquo; or the &ldquo;Company&rdquo;; stock code: &ldquo;LINK&rdquo;) has successfully concluded its annual general meeting of shareholders on Friday morning the 26th of April. Shareholders approved to pay a record high dividend of Rp674 billion for FY18, equating to a 60% dividend payout ratio (DPR) of normalized Net Profit. The dividend payout will be Rp232 per share based on existing shares excluding treasury stock. The proposed dividend of Rp674 billion is Rp170 billion more and an absolute +34% increase from Link Net&rsquo;s FY17 dividend of Rp503 billion.</p>

<p>Link Net management believe that the Company&rsquo;s Board of Directors and Commissioners needs to be representative of the make up of the share register and be comprised of both financial and technically skilled professionals.</p>

<p>Shareholders have approved the appointment of Desmond Poon to Link Net&rsquo;s Board of Directors. Desmond has distinguished himself as Link Net&rsquo;s Chief Technology Officer (CTO), a role which he has held for the past 8 years. He played a key role in growing the business from 550,000 home passes and 193,000 subscribers in 2011 to 2,200,000 home passes and 595,000 subscribers in 2018. He oversees the product planning, as well as engineering and operations of the company. Prior to joining Link Net, he was the Vice President of Network Engineering in Starhub in Singapore, where he held similar responsibilities.</p>

<p>Shareholders have approved the appointment of Suvir Varma as a commissioner on Link Net&rsquo;s Board of Commissioners. Suvir knows Link Net well having served the company as an Independent Director up until the AGMS. He is an ex Senior Partner of Bain &amp; Company, where he led the firm&rsquo;s business focused on Financial Investors across Asia Pacific. He has more than 20 years of experience across consulting and finance-related roles focusing on strategic developments and operational improvements. We warmly welcome both Desmond and Suvir to our Board of Directors and Board of Commissioners and look forward to utilizing their robust skills and expertise across our business.</p>

<p>Shareholders accepted the resignations of Henry Riady from the Board of Directors and Ali Chendra from the Board of Commissioners. We thank both of them for their service on Link Net boards. Likewise Shareholders accepted the resignation of Suvir Varma as an Independent Director due to his appointment to the Board of Commissioners.</p>

<p>Jonathan Parapak will assume the role of President Independent Commissioner.</p>

<p><br />
<strong><u>About PT Link Net Tbk</u></strong><br />
PT Link Net Tbk (&quot;Link Net&quot;), owns and operates a high-speed broadband network in Indonesia, offering high speed internet and cable tv to both residential and enterprise clients.</p>

<p>Learn more at&nbsp;<a href="http://ir.linknet.co.id/" target="_blank">www.ir.linknet.co.id</a></p>

<p>For further information, please contact:<br />
Joel Ellis<br />
Head of Investor Relations<br />
PT Link Net Tbk<br />
Tel: +62 812 911 77785<br />
Email: Joel.Ellis@linknet.co.id</p>', NULL, TRUE, ' PT Link Net Tbk (“Link Net” or the “Company”; stock code: “LINK”) has successfully concluded its annual general meeting of shareholders on Friday morning the 26th of April.', NULL, ' 2021-12-02 01:32:26', ' 2026-05-27 14:13:12', ' 2019-04-27', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', ' daffaprayodi@gmail.com', 3, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (35, ' Link Net Dukung Peningkatan Layanan Kesehatan di Nusa Tenggara Timur (NTT)', ' Link Net Dukung Peningkatan Layanan Kesehatan di Nusa Tenggara Timur (NTT)', ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/csr/csr-peduli-3.png', ' link-net-dukung-peningkatan-layanan-kesehatan-di-nusa-tenggara-timur-ntt', ' In order to carry out corporate social responsibility, the Company gave an ambulance to the St. Antonius Jopu, Ende - NTT, which is managed by the Efata Ende Foundation.', ' Dalam rangka kegiatan tanggung jawab sosial perusahaan Perseroan memberikan satu unit ambulans kepada RS St. Antonius Jopu, Ende – NTT, yang dikelola oleh Yayasan Efata Ende.', ' Aditya Firmansyah', ' <p><strong>18 Nov 2019</strong>&nbsp;- In order to carry out corporate social responsibility, the Company gave an ambulance to the St. Antonius Jopu, Ende - NTT, which is managed by the Efata Ende Foundation. The ambulance was given as a form of the Company&rsquo;s support to improve health services in NTT. The Company is aware of the poor condition of existing health facilities in East Nusa Tenggara (NTT), where there are still many Health Centers, Clinics and Hospitals that has no transportation vehicle such as an ambulance. The Company took the initiative to participate in supporting the improvement of public health services in NTT as part of the &lsquo;First Happiness #ShareTogetherness&rsquo; campaign</p>', ' <p><strong>18 Nov 2019</strong>&nbsp;- Dalam rangka kegiatan tanggung jawab sosial perusahaan Perseroan memberikan satu unit ambulans kepada RS St. Antonius Jopu, Ende &ndash; NTT, yang dikelola oleh Yayasan Efata Ende. Perseroan menyadari minimnya kondisi fasilitas kesehatan yang ada di Nusa Tenggara Timur (NTT), dimana masih banyak Balai Kesehatan, Klinik dan Rumah Sakit yang belum memiliki alat transportasi berupa ambulans. Perseroan mengambil langkah insiatif untuk turut mendukung peningkatan layanan kesehatan masyarakat di NTT sebagai bagian dari kampanye &lsquo;First Happiness #ShareTogetherness&rsquo;.</p>', TRUE, NULL, NULL, ' 2022-01-13 18:54:45', ' 2026-05-27 23:02:14', ' 2019-11-18', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (36, ' Link Net Collaborates with BenihBaik.com to Provide Free Internet Network for Schools', ' Link Net Gandeng BenihBaik.com Untuk Memberikan Jaringan Internet Gratis bagi Sekolah-Sekolah', ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/csr/csr-peduli-1.jpg', ' link-net-gandeng-benihbaik-com-untuk-memberikan-jaringan-internet-gratis-bagi-sekolah-sekolah', ' The Company cooperates with the BenihBaik Foundation in order to provide free internet at the School.', ' Demi Meningkatkan Kualitas Pendidikan, Perseroan melakukan kerjasama dengan Yayasan BenihBaik dalam rangka menyediakan internet gratis di Sekolah.', ' Aditya Firmansyah', ' <p><strong>Descember 6, 2019</strong> - The Company cooperates with the BenihBaik Foundation in order to provide free internet at the School. BenihBaik.com is a fundraising platform to help others who need a helping hand. This cooperation program is a Social Responsibility program carried out by the Company in harmony with the First Happines #ShareTogetherness campaign movement. As a public company the Company is committed to always trying to increase its contribution, both to shareholders and stakeholders at extensively.</p>

<p>The collaboration with BenihBaik.com is carried out in order to invite the Company&rsquo;s customers to share with others who aim to provide internet networks in schools located in the operational areas of the Company, and support the advancement of the Education quality in the digital era. Going forward, the Company will continue to increase the company&rsquo;s contribution in various forms of social activities that have a positive impact on the people of Indonesia</p>', ' <p><strong>6 Desember 2019</strong> - Demi Meningkatkan Kualitas Pendidikan, Perseroan melakukan kerjasama dengan Yayasan BenihBaik dalam rangka menyediakan internet gratis di Sekolah. BenihBaik.com merupakan salah satu platform penggalangan dana untuk membantu orang lain yang membutuhkan uluran tangan. Program kerjasama ini merupakan program Tanggung Jawab&nbsp;&nbsp;Sosial yang dilakukan oleh Perseroan selaras dengan gerakan kampanye First Happines #ShareTogetherness. Perseroan sebagai perusahaan publik berkomitmen untuk selalu berusaha meningkatkan kontribusinya, baik ke shareholders maupun stakeholders secara luas.</p>

<p>Kerja sama dengan BenihBaik.com dilakukan dalam rangka mengajak pelanggan Perseroan untuk turut berbagi dengan sesama yang bertujuan memberikan jaringan internet di sekolah-sekolah yang berada di wilayah operasional Perseroan, serta mendukung kemajuan dunia Pendidikan di era digital. Kedepannya, Perseroan akan terus meningkatkan kontribusi perusahaan dalam berbagai bentuk kegiatan sosial yang berdampak positif bagi masyarakat Indonesia</p>', TRUE, NULL, NULL, ' 2022-01-13 19:09:50', ' 2026-05-27 12:34:55', ' 2019-12-06', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (37, ' Multivitamin & Personal Protective Equipment Donations', ' Donasi Multivitamin & Alat Pelindung Diri', ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/csr/csr-peduli-2.jpg', ' donasi-multivitamin-alat-pelindung-diri', ' As a step of concern for medical personnel who are handling the Covid-19 pandemic, the Company in 2020 donated multivitamin products to several Covid-19 referral hospitals', ' Sebagai langkah kepedulian terhadap para tenaga medis yang sedang menangani pandemi Covid-19, Perseroan pada tahun 2020 menyumbang produk multivitamin ke beberapa Rumah Sakit rujukan Covid-19', ' Aditya Firmansyah', ' <p><b>April 19, 2020 -&nbsp;</b>As a step of concern for medical personnel who are handling the Covid-19 pandemic, the Company in 2020 donated multivitamin products to several Covid-19 referral hospitals such as:</p>

<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Fatmawati Hospital, Jakarta<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Pelni Petamburan Hospital, Jakarta<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Siloam Kelapa Dua Hospital, Tangerang<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Mitra Keluarga Jatiasih Hospital, Bekasi</p>

<p>The company handed in 63,480 multivitamins to 4 (four) COVID-19 referral hospitals and gave 3 (three) months free subscription to First Media services to 3,013 medical personnel. In addition to multivitamins, the Company in the CSR program Cares for Medical Workers donated 4,500 Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) for medical workers, which were given to 12 COVID referral hospitals from 10 cities in Indonesia, including Jakarta, Bandung, Cirebon, Semarang, Yogyakarta, Surabaya, Sidoarjo, Malang, Medan and Batam.</p>

<p>The total supply of 4,500 Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) in the form of hazmat suits, as many as 500 units were submitted to Siloam Hospitals Mampang Jakarta, 400 units to Bhayangkara General Hospital. I R. Said Sukanto Jakarta, Al-Islam Hospital Bandung, RSD Gunung Jati Cirebon, RSUP Dr. Kariadi Semarang, RSUP Dr. Sardjito Yogyakarta, RSUD Dr. Soetomo Surabaya, Waru Sidoarjo Mitra Mitra Hospital, Malang Lawang Hospital, Adam Malik General Hospital Medan, and 200 units for Batam Authority Hospital, and 200 units for Embung Fatimah Hospital Batam.</p>

<p>Through this multivitamin and Personal Protective Equipment donations, the Company wants to help maintain the health and immunity of medical personnel. As well as a gesture of utmost respect for the dedication of the work that has been done by medical personnel who have struggled to treat covid-19 patients.<br />
&nbsp;</p>', ' <p><strong>19 April 2020</strong> - Sebagai langkah kepedulian terhadap para tenaga medis yang sedang menangani pandemi Covid-19, Perseroan pada tahun 2020 menyumbang produk multivitamin ke beberapa Rumah Sakit rujukan Covid-19 seperti:</p>

<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rumah Sakit Fatmawati, Jakarta<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rumah Sakit Pelni Petamburan, Jakarta<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rumah Sakit Siloam Kelapa Dua, Tangerang<br />
&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rumah Sakit Mitra Keluarga Jatiasih, Bekasi</p>

<p>Perseroan menyerahkan 63.480 multivitamin ke 4 (empat) rumah sakit rujukan COVID-19 dan pemberian gratis berlangganan layanan First Media selama 3 (tiga) bulan kepada 3.013 tenaga medis. Selain multivitamin, Perseroan dalam program CSR Peduli Tenaga Medis mendonasikan sebanyak 4.500 Alat Pelindung Diri (APD) bagi para tenaga medis, yang diberikan ke 12 rumah sakit rujukan COVID19 dari 10 kota di Indonesia, diantaranya Jakarta, Bandung, Cirebon, Semarang, Yogyakarta, Surabaya, Sidoarjo, Malang, Medan dan Batam.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Dari total penyediaan 4.500 Alat Pelindung Diri (APD) berupa hazmat suit, sebanyak 500 unit diserahkan ke Siloam Hospitals Mampang Jakarta, 400 unit untuk RSU Bhayangkara Tk. I R. Said Sukanto Jakarta, RS Al-Islam Bandung, RSD Gunung Jati Cirebon, RSUP Dr. Kariadi Semarang, RSUP Dr. Sardjito Yogyakarta, RSUD Dr. Soetomo Surabaya, RS Mitra Keluarga Waru Sidoarjo, RSUD Lawang Malang, RSUP Adam Malik Medan, serta 200 unit untuk RS Otorita Batam, dan 200 unit untuk RSUD Embung Fatimah Batam.</p>

<p>Melalui sumbangan multivitamin dan Alat Pelindung Diri ini Perseroan ingin membantu menjaga kesehatan dan imunitas para tenaga medis. Sekaligus sebagai sikap penghormatan sebesar-besarnya atas dedikasi pekerjaan yang telah dilakukan oleh para tenaga medis yang sudah berjuang merawat pasien covid-19.&nbsp;</p>', TRUE, NULL, NULL, ' 2022-01-13 19:23:12', ' 2026-05-27 11:31:21', ' 2020-04-19', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (38, ' Link Net Supports West Java Community Health and Economic Recovery', ' Link Net Dukung Kesehatan dan Pemulihan Ekonomi Masyarakat Jawa Barat', ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/csr/Link-Net-Dukung-Kesehatan-dan-Pemulihan-Ekonomi-Masyarakat-Jawa-Barat.jpg', ' link-net-dukung-kesehatan-dan-pemulihan-ekonomi-masyarakat-jawa-barat', ' PT Link Net Tbk with the First Media brand together with the Bandung City Communication and Information Office (Diskominfo) and the Bandung City Health Office held a Covid-19 vaccination', ' PT Link Net Tbk dengan brand First Media bersama Dinas Komunikasi dan Informatika (Diskominfo) Kota Bandung serta Dinas Kesehatan Kota Bandung menggelar vaksinasi Covid-19', ' Aditya Firmansyah', ' <p><strong>November 19, 2021 -&nbsp;</strong>After providing support for the Bandung City Government&#39;s first dose of Covid-19 vaccination with the AstraZeneca vaccine, on 11-13 August 2021, PT Link Net Tbk with the First Media brand together with the Bandung City Communications and Information Office (Diskominfo) and the Bandung City Health Office held another vaccination for the second dose, last November 9-10, at Taman Dewi Sartika, Bandung City Hall, West Java.</p>

<p>This mass vaccination is First Media&#39;s support for public health during the pandemic as well as to support the Bandung City Government&#39;s Covid-19 vaccination acceleration program. From the first dose of mass vaccination, a total of 1,169 people have received the vaccine. While the total receipt of the second dose of vaccination reached 967 people.</p>

<p>The second dose of vaccination was reviewed directly by the Mayor of Bandung, and was held in conjunction with the handover ceremony for Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) broadband internet services and free WiFi from PT Link Net Tbk to the Head of the Bandung City Communication and Information Office (Diskominfo). by the Mayor of Bandung H. Oded M. Danial, SAP, and representatives of the management of PT Link Net Tbk including representatives of First Media Business Unit 3 (West Java).<br />
&nbsp;</p>', ' <p><strong>19 November 2021 -&nbsp;</strong>Setelah memberikan dukungan dalam kegiatan vaksinasi Covid-19 dosis pertama Pemerintah Kota Bandung dengan jenis vaksin AstraZeneca, pada tanggal 11-13 Agustus 2021, PT Link Net Tbk dengan brand First Media bersama Dinas Komunikasi dan Informatika (Diskominfo) Kota Bandung serta Dinas Kesehatan Kota Bandung kembali menggelar vaksinasi untuk dosis kedua, tanggal 9-10 November lalu, di Taman Dewi Sartika, Balai Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat.</p>

<p>Vaksinasi massal ini merupakan dukungan First Media terhadap kesehatan masyarakat di masa pandemi sekaligus dalam rangka mendukung program percepatan vaksinasi Covid 19 Pemerintah Kota Bandung. Dari kegiatan vaksinasi massal dosis pertama, total vaksin telah diterima oleh 1.169 orang. Sementara total penerimaan vaksinasi dosis kedua mencapai 967 orang.</p>

<p>Kegiatan vaksinasi dosis kedua ditinjau langsung oleh Wali Kota Bandung, dan diselenggarakan bersamaan dengan acara serah terima Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) layanan internet broadband dan WiFi gratis dari PT Link Net Tbk kepada Kepala Dinas Komunikasi dan Informatika (Diskominfo) Kota Bandung, yang turut disaksikan oleh Wali Kota Bandung H. Oded M. Danial, S.A.P, dan perwakilan manajemen PT Link Net Tbk termasuk perwakilan First Media Business Unit 3 (West Java).</p>', TRUE, NULL, NULL, ' 2022-01-13 19:58:27', ' 2026-05-27 21:55:41', ' 2021-11-19', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', 4, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (40, ' ZTE Collaborates with Link Net’s First Media to Boost Network Services for Information Superhighway in Jayabaya Project', ' Kolaborasi ZTE dengan Link Net Tingkatkan Layanan Jaringan Proyek Information Superhighway Jayabaya', ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/2022/press-release/Kolaborasi-PT-Link-Net-Tbk-dan-ZTE.webp', ' kolaborasi-zte-dengan-link-net-tingkatkan-layanan-jaringan-proyek-information-superhighway-jayabaya', ' ZTE continues to collaborate with PT Link Net Tbk to deliver better digital experience in boosting Link Net’s network service, leveraging ZXONE 9700 DWDM', ' ZTE melanjutkan kolaborasi dengan PT Link Net Tbk untuk menghadirkan pengalaman digital yang lebih baik dan meningkatkan layanan jaringan Link Net dengan memanfaatkan ZXONE 9700 DWDM', ' Aditya Firmansyah', ' <ul>
	<li>ZTE continues to collaborate with PT Link Net Tbk to deliver better digital experience in boosting Link Net&rsquo;s network service, leveraging ZXONE 9700 DWDM</li>
	<li>This collaboration aims to support the building of the information superhighway from Jakarta to Surabaya (Jayabaya Project)</li>
	<li>ZXONE 9700 DWDM has been rated as a &ldquo;leader&rdquo; on the core packet-optical platform by GlobalData in 2017</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Jakarta, 27 April 2022 </strong>&ndash;&nbsp;ZTE Corporation (0763.HK / 000063.SZ), a major international provider of telecommunications, enterprise and consumer technology solutions for the mobile internet, today announced that it has collaborated with PT Link Net Tbk (&ldquo;LINK&rdquo;), one of the leading cable TV and fixed broadband internet providers in Indonesia with the brand &ldquo;First Media&rdquo;, to deliver excellent digital experiences with ZXONE 9700 DWDM in boosting Link Net&rsquo;s network services in Jayabaya Project.</p>

<p>ZXONE 9700 DWDM, featuring an 100G and beyond 100G-oriented brand-new universal switching equipment, can support 100G/400G/1T transmission rate, with an aim to build the information superhighway from Jakarta to Surabaya. Also, it can support 340km+ ultra-long haul submarine fiber optic cable and provide robust protection for customer services.</p>

<p>&quot;The ZXONE 9700 DWDM series introduces more advanced technologies into transport infrastructure networks, which will help Link Net to build a packet-oriented, 100G-enabled and flexible transport network,&rdquo; said <strong>Steven Lee, Sales Director of ZTE Indonesia</strong>. &ldquo;We are honored to continue our collaboration with Link Net and strive to lead innovations to provide better digital experiences and improve network services for our customers.&rdquo;</p>

<p><strong>Marlo Budiman, President Director and CEO of PT Link Net Tbk </strong>said, &ldquo;We believe the collaboration of Link Net and ZTE as a trusted partner will be able to provide advanced network services for excellent digital experiences for our customers. This partnership will help us to provide network services with higher stability and reliability, especially for our customers in Java. We aim to continue to provide cable TV and fixed broadband internet solutions to support the digitalization in Indonesia.&rdquo;</p>

<p>The technological solution provided by ZTE through this submarine network innovation, further complements the existing network on land to prevent and minimize potential network issues. This positive impact will be received directly by all Link Net customers from the enterprise and residential segments.</p>

<p>The collaboration between ZTE and Link Net has been running since 2017 through such ZTE&rsquo;s products as ZTE DWDM, GPON, and BRAS. The ZXONE 9700 DWDM solution will further support the optimization of the Link Net network, especially in Java. In 2021, Link Net has succeeded in adding 190,000 homes passed, bringing a total network of 2.87 million homes passed across 23 cities in Java, Medan, Batam, and Bali.</p>

<p>ZXONE 9700 DWDM has been rated as &ldquo;Leader&rdquo; on the core packet-optical platform by GlobalData, world-renowned telecommunication, software, and IT service consulting company. According to the report, ZXONE 9700 has the strongest switching capacity and can provide the highest number of dense wavelength division multiplexing (DWDM) lines among similar products.&nbsp;</p>

<p>To date, ZTE is the first manufacturer to have a product rated as &ldquo;Leader&rdquo; in both the categories of core packet transport and metro optical transport. The company, especially in this Jakarta-Surabaya (Jayabaya) Project will continue to construct Indonesia&rsquo;s networks to provide a wider coverage for telecommunication and broadband services.&nbsp;</p>', ' <ul>
	<li>ZTE melanjutkan kolaborasi dengan PT Link Net Tbk untuk menghadirkan pengalaman digital yang lebih baik dan meningkatkan layanan jaringan Link Net dengan memanfaatkan ZXONE 9700 DWDM</li>
	<li>Kerja sama ini bertujuan untuk mendukung pembangunan information superhighway Jakarta-Surabaya (Jayabaya Project)</li>
	<li>ZXONE 9700 DWDM diberikan predikat sebagai &quot;pemimpin&quot; di core packet-optical platform oleh GlobalData pada tahun 2017</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Jakarta, 27 April 2022 </strong>&ndash; ZTE Corporation (0763.HK/000063.SZ), perusahaan global terkemuka penyedia solusi teknologi telekomunikasi, enterprise, dan konsumen untuk internet seluler, mengumumkan kolaborasinya dengan PT Link Net Tbk (&ldquo;LINK&rdquo;). Kerja sama ini bertujuan untuk memberikan pengalaman digital yang lebih baik dengan menggunakan ZXONE 9700 DWDM dalam meningkatkan layanan jaringan Link Net di Proyek Jayabaya.</p>

<p>Penggunaan ZXONE 9700 DWDM, peralatan switching universal baru berorientasi 100G atau lebih yang dapat mendukung kecepatan transmisi 100G/400G/1T, adalah untuk membangun information superhighway dari Jakarta ke Surabaya. Produk ini juga mampu mendukung pengaplikasian kabel serat optik bawah laut jarak jauh lebih dari 340 km, sehingga layanan jaringan untuk pelanggan bisa terlindungi dengan lebih baik.</p>

<p>&quot;Seri ZXONE 9700 DWDM memperkenalkan teknologi yang lebih canggih untuk jaringan infrastruktur transportasi (transport infrastructure networks), yang akan membantu Link Net membangun jaringan transportasi yang packet-oriented, mendukung 100G, dan fleksibel,&quot; ujar <strong>Steven Lee, Sales Director of ZTE Indonesia</strong>. &ldquo;Sebuah kehormatan bagi kami dapat melanjutkan kolaborasi dengan Link Net. Kami senantiasa terus berusaha memimpin inovasi guna memberikan pengalaman digital yang lebih baik dan meningkatkan layanan jaringan bagi pelanggan kami.&rdquo;</p>

<p><strong>Marlo Budiman, Presiden Direktur dan CEO PT Link Net Tbk </strong>mengatakan, &ldquo;Kami percaya kolaborasi Link Net dan ZTE sebagai mitra terpercaya akan mampu mendukung penyediaan layanan jaringan yang andal untuk pengalaman digital terbaik bagi pelanggan. Kemitraan ini akan membantu Link Net dalam memberikan layanan jaringan dengan stabilitas dan reliabilitas yang lebih tinggi, terutama bagi pelanggan Link Net di pulau Jawa. Kemitraan ini turut mendukung komitmen Link Net untuk terus memberikan solusi layanan cable TV dan fixed broadband internet dalam mendukung digitalisasi di Indonesia.&rdquo;</p>

<p>Solusi teknologi yang diberikan oleh ZTE melalui inovasi submarine network ini, semakin melengkapi jaringan yang ada di darat untuk mencegah dan meminimalisir potensi gangguan jaringan. Dampak positif ini akan dirasakan secara langsung oleh seluruh pelanggan Link Net dari segmen enterprise dan residensial.</p>

<p>Kerja sama antara ZTE dan Link Net telah berjalan sejak tahun 2017 melalui produk-produk seperti ZTE DWDM, GPON, dan BRAS. Solusi ZXONE 9700 DWDM akan semakin mendukung optimalisasi jaringan Link Net khususnya di pulau Jawa. Pada tahun 2021, Link Net telah berhasil menambahkan 190 ribu homes passed, menjadikan total jaringan sebesar 2,87 juta homes passed yang tersebar di 23 kota di Jawa, Medan, Batam, dan Bali.&nbsp;</p>

<p>ZXONE 9700 DWDM telah diberikan predikat sebagai &quot;pemimpin&quot; pada core packet-optical platform oleh GlobalData, perusahaan konsultan telekomunikasi, perangkat lunak, dan layanan yang terkemuka di dunia. Menurut laporan tersebut, ZXONE 9700 DWDM dari ZTE menyediakan kapasitas switching terkuat dan jumlah dense wavelength division multiplexing (DWDM) tertinggi di antara produk serupa.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Hingga saat ini, ZTE adalah produsen pertama untuk produk yang dinilai sebagai &ldquo;pemimpin&rdquo; dalam kategori core packet transport dan metro optical transport. ZTE akan terus membangun jaringan di Indonesia untuk menyediakan cakupan yang lebih luas untuk layanan telekomunikasi dan broadband, khususnya dalam Proyek Jakarta-Surabaya (Jayabaya).</p>', TRUE, ' Kolaborasi ZTE dengan Link Net Tingkatkan Layanan Jaringan Proyek Information Superhighway Jayabaya', ' First Media, Linknet Enterprise, Kerja sama ZTE dengan PT Link Net, Tbk', ' 2022-05-05 17:23:41', ' 2026-05-27 13:52:50', ' 2022-04-27', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', ' aditya.firmansyah@biz.linknet.co.id', 8, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (41, ' Link Net FY2021 Financial and Operational Results', ' Hasil Pencapaian Finansial dan Operasional Link Net FY2021', ' https://www.linknet.co.id/storage/files/images/media_activities/2022/press-release/pencapaian-linknet-2021.webp', ' hasil-pencapaian-finansial-dan-operasional-link-net-2021', ' Link Net booked revenue of Rp4.5tn in FY2021, growing 10.4% compared to Rp4.05tn in FY2020.', ' Link Net membukukan pendapatan sebesar Rp4,5 triliun pada FY2021, bertumbuh 10,4% dibandingkan dengan Rp4,05 triliun di FY2020.', ' Aditya Firmansyah', ' <h3><strong>Link Net FY2021 Financial and Operational Results</strong></h3>

<ul>
	<li>Revenue Grew 10.4% Year-on-Year</li>
	<li>EBITDA Grew 8.5% Year-on-Year</li>
	<li>Link Net&rsquo;s enterprise business grew 25% Year-on-Year</li>
	<li>Link Net added 190k additional home passes to its network in FY2021</li>
</ul>

<p>PT Link Net Tbk (&ldquo;Link Net&rdquo; or the Company; stock code: &ldquo;LINK&rdquo;)</p>

<p><strong>Financial &amp; Operational:</strong></p>

<p>Link Net booked revenue of Rp4.5tn in FY2021, growing 10.4% compared to Rp4.05tn in FY2020. Revenue strengthened in 4Q2021 with Link Net booking revenue of Rp1.2tn, growing 11.8% compared to Rp1.1tn in 4Q2020. The company&rsquo;s EBITDA was Rp2.5tn in FY2021, growing 8.5% compared with Rp2.3tn in FY2020. Link Net booked Net Profit of Rp885bn in FY2021.</p>

<p>EBITDA and Net Profit margins were 56.0% and 19.8% respectively. The company had operating cash flow of Rp1.97tn in FY2021, growing 6.1% compared to FY2020. The Company&rsquo;s Net cash position was Rp271bn as at the end of 2021</p>

<table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%;">
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="text-align:center;background-color:#F2BF11;color:#fff;">Financials (IDR bn)</td>
